
                <html xmlns:o='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office' xmlns:w='urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40'>
                <head>
                    <meta charset='utf-8'>
                    <title>Practice</title>
                    <style>
                        body { font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt; }
                        table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; }
                        td, th { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; }
                        .question-container { margin-bottom: 20px; page-break-inside: avoid; }
                        .header-badges span { display: inline-block; padding: 4px 8px; margin-right: 5px; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 10pt; background: #eee; border: 1px solid #ccc; }
                        .complexity-Easy { background-color: #dcfce7; color: #15803d; }
                        .complexity-Medium { background-color: #fef9c3; color: #a16207; }
                        .complexity-Hard { background-color: #fee2e2; color: #b91c1c; }
                    </style>
                </head>
                <body>
            
            <div style="padding: 20px;">
                <h1 style="text-align: center; border-bottom: 2px solid #ccc; padding-bottom: 10px;">Practice</h1>
                
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q1</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Queue Operation Basics</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which operation is used to remove an element from a queue?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Push</p></li><li><p>Pop</p></li><li><p>Dequeue</p></li><li><p>Insert</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Dequeue</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q2</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Front and Rear</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In a queue, insertion happens at ___ and deletion happens at ___.</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Front, Front</p></li><li><p>Rear, Rear</p></li><li><p>Rear, Front</p></li><li><p>Front, Rear</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Rear, Front</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q3</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Priority Queue vs Queue</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Main difference between queue and priority queue is</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Size</p></li><li><p>Data type</p></li><li><p>Memory usage</p></li><li><p>Order of deletion</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Order of deletion</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q4</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Queue Empty Condition</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What does this condition check?</p><pre><code>if(front == -1 || front &gt; rear)</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Queue full</p></li><li><p>Queue empty</p></li><li><p>Queue partially full</p></li><li><p>Circular queue</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Queue empty</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q5</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Circular Queue Index Movement</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the new value of rear?</p><pre><code>#define SIZE 5
int q[SIZE];
int front = 3, rear = 3;
rear = (rear + 1) % SIZE;
q[rear] = 10;</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>3</p></li><li><p>4</p></li><li><p>0</p></li><li><p>2</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>4</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q6</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Queue State Analysis</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the number of elements in the queue?</p><pre><code>front = 0; rear = -1;
rear++;
rear++;
front++;</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>0</p></li><li><p>1</p></li><li><p>2</p></li><li><p>3</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>1</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q7</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Dequeue Output</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the output?</p><pre><code>int q[] = {5, 10, 15, 20};
front = 1;
printf("%d", q[front++]);</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>10</p></li><li><p>5</p></li><li><p>15</p></li><li><p>20</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>10</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q8</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Linked List Queue Dequeue</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What happens if front was the only node?</p><pre><code>struct node *temp = front;
front = front-&gt;next;
free(temp);</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>rear becomes NULL automatically</p></li><li><p>rear still points to freed memory</p><p></p></li><li><p>front becomes NULL but rear unchanged</p></li><li><p>Both front and rear become NULL</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>front becomes NULL but rear unchanged</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q9</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Linear Queue Tracing</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the output?</p><pre><code>int q[5] = {10, 20, 30, 40, 50};
int front = 1, rear = 3;
front++;
q[rear++] = 60;
printf("%d %d", front, rear);</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>1 4</p></li><li><p>2 4</p></li><li><p>2 3</p></li><li><p>1 3</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>2 4</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q10</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Queue Empty Logic Trap</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the output?</p><pre><code>int front = 2, rear = 2;
front++;
front++;
if (front &gt; rear)
    printf("Empty");
else
    printf("Not Empty");</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Empty</p></li><li><p>Not Empty</p></li><li><p>Undefined</p></li><li><p>Runtime Error</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Empty</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q11</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What does this snippet return for a BST node?</p><pre><code>Node* g(Node* r) {
  Node* c = r-&gt;left;
  while(c &amp;&amp; c-&gt;right) c = c-&gt;right;
  return c;
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>In-order Predecessor</p></li><li><p>The minimum leaf</p></li><li><p>In-order Successor</p></li><li><p>The root of the tree</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>In-order Predecessor</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q12</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What does this C++ snippet return?</p><pre><code>int c(Node* r, int low, int high) {
  if(!r) return 0;
  int cnt = (r-&gt;val &gt;= low &amp;&amp; r-&gt;val &lt;= high);
  return cnt + c(r-&gt;left, low, high) + c(r-&gt;right, low, high);
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Nodes within the range [low, high]</p></li><li><p>The sum of values in range</p></li><li><p>Total nodes in the tree</p></li><li><p>The maximum value in range</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Nodes within the range [low, high]</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q13</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the time complexity of this BST search snippet?</p><pre><code>bool s(Node* r, int k) {
  while(r) {
    if(r-&gt;val == k) return true;
    r = (k &lt; r-&gt;val) ? r-&gt;left : r-&gt;right;
  }
  return false;
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>O(logN) average, O(N) worst</p></li><li><p>O(N) always</p></li><li><p>O(H²) where H is height</p></li><li><p>O(1) always</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>O(logN) average, O(N) worst</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q14</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Given the Pre-order traversal of a BST: 15, 10, 12, 20, 18, 25 What is the In-order traversal of this tree?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>10,15,12,18,25,20</p></li><li><p>25,20,18,15,12,10</p></li><li><p>10,12,15,18,20,25</p></li><li><p>15,10,12,18,20,25</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>10,12,15,18,20,25</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q15</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In a Binary Search Tree (BST), what is the time complexity of finding the minimum element in a skewed tree with N nodes?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>O(1)</p></li><li><p>O(logN)</p></li><li><p>O(N)</p></li><li><p>O(NlogN)</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>O(N)</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q16</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which node is the In-order Successor of a node X in a BST if node X has a non-empty right subtree?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>The parent of X</p></li><li><p>The leftmost node in the right subtree</p></li><li><p>The rightmost node in the left subtree</p></li><li><p>The right child of X</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>The leftmost node in the right subtree</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q17</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What does this function return for a BST root?</p><pre><code>int m(Node* r) {
  while(r &amp;&amp; r-&gt;right) r = r-&gt;right;
  return r-&gt;val;
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Total node count</p></li><li><p>The root value</p></li><li><p>The minimum value</p></li><li><p>The maximum value</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>The maximum value</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q18</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the result of solve(root, 20) if the root data is 15?</p><pre><code>void solve(Node* r, int k) {
  if(!r) return;
  if(r-&gt;val &lt; k) solve(r-&gt;right, k);
  cout &lt;&lt; r-&gt;val &lt;&lt; " ";
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Prints 15 then searches right</p></li><li><p>Prints 15 after its right subtree</p></li><li><p>Causes a segmentation fault</p></li><li><p>Prints nothing</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Prints 15 after its right subtree</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q19</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In this deletion helper, what happens if r-&gt;left is NULL?</p><pre><code>Node* del(Node* r) {
  Node* temp = r-&gt;right;
  delete r;
  return temp;
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Deletes the current node and returns its right child</p></li><li><p>Returns NULL always</p></li><li><p>Deletes the entire right subtree</p></li><li><p>Causes a memory leak</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Deletes the current node and returns its right child</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q20</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Binary search tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the purpose of the following snippet?</p><pre><code>void upd(Node* r) {
  if(!r) return;
  upd(r-&gt;left);
  r-&gt;val += 10;
  upd(r-&gt;right);
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Breaks the BST property</p></li><li><p>Increments all values by 10</p></li><li><p>Only updates the root</p></li><li><p>Finds nodes greater than 10</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Increments all values by 10</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
