                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In Double Hashing, if h2(k) is the second hash function, why is it critical that h2(k) is relatively prime to the table size m?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>To reduce the load factor</p></li><li><p>To make the hash function faster</p></li><li><p>To allow for easier deletion</p></li><li><p>To ensure h2(k) never returns 0</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>To ensure h2(k) never returns 0</p></div>

