                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q83</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tree traversal</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the output for a tree with root 1, left child 2, right child 3?</p><pre><code>void t(Node* r) {
  if(!r) return;
  t(r-&gt;left); t(r-&gt;right);
  cout &lt;&lt; r-&gt;data &lt;&lt; " ";
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>1 2 3</p></li><li><p>2 3 1</p></li><li><p>2 1 3</p></li><li><p>3 2 1</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>2 3 1</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q84</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tree traversal</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In a Post-order traversal, which node is always the very last to be visited?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>The Root node</p></li><li><p>The leftmost leaf</p></li><li><p>The node with the maximum value</p></li><li><p>The rightmost leaf</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>The Root node</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q85</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Tree traversal</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which data structure is most commonly used to implement Level-order traversal iteratively?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Priority Queue</p></li><li><p>Stack</p></li><li><p>Queue</p></li><li><p>Linked List</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Queue</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q86</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which of the following is NOT a property of a Red-Black Tree?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Every node is either red or black</p></li><li><p>The root is always black</p></li><li><p>All leaves (NULL nodes) are black</p></li><li><p>Every red node must have two black children</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Every red node must have two black children</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q87</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In a Red-Black Tree, what is the maximum height of a tree with n nodes?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>log₂(n)</p></li><li><p style="text-align: left;">2 × log₂(n)</p></li><li><p>n</p></li><li><p>n/2</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p style="text-align: left;">2 × log₂(n)</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q88</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the primary purpose of coloring nodes red or black in a Red-Black Tree?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>To reduce memory usage</p></li><li><p>To speed up searching</p></li><li><p>To maintain balanced height</p></li><li><p>To simplify insertion code</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>To maintain balanced height</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q89</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">AVL tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Trace the code: What node becomes root after <strong>rotateRight(10)</strong> where 10's left is 5, and 5's right is 7?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>5</p></li><li><p>7</p></li><li><p>NULL</p></li><li><p>10</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>5</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q90</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">AVL tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What does this C++ snippet check?</p><pre><code>if (bf &lt; -1 &amp;&amp; getB(n-&gt;right) &gt; 0)</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>LR case</p></li><li><p>RR case</p></li><li><p>LL case</p></li><li><p>RL case</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>RL case</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q91</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">AVL tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>If a node has a balance factor of -2 and its right child has a balance factor of 1, which rotation sequence is needed?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Right-Left (RL) Rotation</p></li><li><p>Single Left Rotation</p></li><li><p>Single Right Rotation</p></li><li><p>Left-Right (LR) Rotation</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Right-Left (RL) Rotation</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q92</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Heap</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the time complexity to build a heap from an unordered array of N elements using the bottom-up heapify method?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>O(NlogN)</p></li><li><p>O(N²)</p></li><li><p>O(N)</p></li><li><p>O(logN)</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>O(N)</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q93</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Heap</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>In a Max-Heap represented by an array (1-based indexing), if a node is at index i, what is the index of its right child?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>i/2</p></li><li><p>2i</p></li><li><p>2i + 1</p></li><li><p>2i − 1</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>2i + 1</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q94</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Heap</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which operation is performed immediately after the root element is removed from a Max-Heap?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>The root is replaced by the last element in the array</p></li><li><p>The tree is re-scanned for the next maximum</p></li><li><p>The children of the root are swapped</p></li><li><p>The root is replaced by its left child</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>The root is replaced by the last element in the array</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q95</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">AVL tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What does this C++ snippet calculate?</p><pre><code>int getB(Node* n) {
  if (!n) return 0;
  return height(n-&gt;left) - height(n-&gt;right);
}</code></pre><p></p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>The balance factor</p></li><li><p>The total height</p></li><li><p style="text-align: left;">The node's value</p></li><li><p>The leaf count</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>The balance factor</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q96</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the time complexity of insertion in a Red-Black Tree?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>O(n)</p></li><li><p>O(n log n)</p></li><li><p>O(log n)</p></li><li><p>O(1)</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>O(log n)</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q97</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which traversal will display the sorted order of elements stored in a Red-Black Tree?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p style="text-align: left;">Preorder</p></li><li><p>Postorder</p></li><li><p>Level order</p></li><li><p>Inorder</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Inorder</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q98</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which rotation is commonly used during Red-Black Tree insertion fixing in C++?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Left and Right rotations</p></li><li><p style="text-align: left;">Single rotation only</p></li><li><p>Double rotation only</p></li><li><p>Circular rotation</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Left and Right rotations</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q99</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Red Black Tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>Which case during insertion requires a Left-Right or Right-Left rotation?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>Parent and uncle are red</p></li><li><p>Node is an inner child</p></li><li><p>Node is root</p></li><li><p>Node is a leaf</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>Node is an inner child</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
                <div class="question-container">
                    <div class="header-badges">
                        <span>Q100</span>
                        <span class="complexity-Medium">Medium</span>
                        <span style="background-color: #eff6ff; color: #1d4ed8;">MCQ</span>
                    </div>

                    <h2 style="font-size: 16pt; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px;">AVL tree</h2>

                    <div style="font-size: 12pt;">
                        <p>What is the minimum number of nodes in an AVL tree of height 3 (where root is height 0)?</p>
                    </div>

                    
                    <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                        <h3>Options:</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p>4</p></li><li><p>15</p></li><li><p>7</p></li><li><p>8</p></li>
                        </ul>
                    </div><div style="margin-top: 10px; font-weight: bold; color: #15803d;">Correct Answer: <p>7</p></div>

                    <hr style="margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid #ccc;" />
                </div>
            
            </div>
        </body></html>